Jenni Evans, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - A group of gunmen opened fire in a drive-by shooting in Prince George Avenue, near Muizenberg, on Tuesday, Cape Town's Mayoral Committee Member for Safety and Security JP Smith said."It was a drive-by shooting involving a Toyota Camry," said Smith.The shooting from the vehicle took place near Capricorn, which is a suburb near Muizenberg.Nobody was injured and it was not clear who the shooters were targeting.The men fled the scene. Police are investigating. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.